<center>
   <br></br>
   <h1>Simple JPS Example</h1>
   <br>
</center>
<font size=4>
<font color="red">
<p>&lt!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0 Final//EN">
<br>&ltHTML>
<br>&ltHEAD>
<br>&ltTITLE>A simple date example&lt/TITLE>
<br>&lt/HEAD>
<br>&ltBODY COLOR=#ffffff>
<br>The time on the server is 
<br>&lt%= new java.util.Date() %>
<br>&lt/BODY>
<br>&lt/HTML></p>
</font>

<p>The tags &lt% and %> are used to denote the beginning and end of a JSP
section.</p>
<br>
<p>The output of this page would look something like the following</p>
<br>
<font color="red">
<p>The time on the server is Thurs March 22 15:15:00 EDT 2001</p>
</font>
</font>
